cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.NA, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing polynomial and rational solutions of linear recurrences and hypergeometric summation, which are symbolic computation problems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes variants of existing algorithms that exploit the structure of solutions and avoid expanding polynomials of high degree, which is a common theme in algorithm design.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the bit complexity of the algorithms and proposes improvements that reduce the dependence on the size of the input.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper deals with the computation of solutions of linear recurrences and hypergeometric summation, which are numerical problems.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve some logical reasoning in the design and analysis of the algorithms.
